ch.epfl.biop.atlas.aligner

Class CancelableAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.epfl.biop.atlas.aligner.CancelableAction
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CreateSliceAction, DeleteLastRegistrationAction, DeleteSliceAction, EditLastRegistrationAction, ExportAtlasSliceToImagePlusAction, ExportDeformationFieldToImagePlusAction, ExportSliceRegionsToFileAction, ExportSliceRegionsToQuPathProjectAction, ExportSliceRegionsToRoiManagerAction, ExportSliceToImagePlusAction, KeySliceOffAction, KeySliceOnAction, LockAndRunOnceSliceAction, MarkActionSequenceBatchAction, MoveSliceAction, RasterDeformationAction, RasterSliceAction, RegisterSliceAction, UnMirrorSliceAction

    public abstract class CancelableAction
extends Object
    Backbone of a cancelable action used for Bdv Slice Positioner This is used in order to: - store the sequence of actions (- for cancellation) - executes actions asynchronously (- for long computations) - keep track of which action is executed on which SliceSources - serialization Convention : an action acts on a single SliceSources object. If multiple SliceSources should be acted on, create as many actions as SliceSources involved (and mark the sequence with @see MarkActionSequenceBatch)
